I believe that both the 02(10) definition and the 05(3) definition could be applied here.

For the first one, 02(10), it could be that Sherlock is referring to how Moriarty's good background and resources, had allowed him access to a broad education and many areas of knowledge via instruction and learning.

However, given Sherlock's previous words about his good birth, the 05 (3) definition could apply here as well. It could also simply mean that he was raised with an excellent social standard of how to move around in that period's society (i.e. scholar-like or a gentleman). Hence, belonging to household name may fit the other definition of having good breeding and education.;

